column1: #Text=[0141] A solution of Example 10A (4.1 g, 14.8 mmol) in a mixture of THF (20 mL) and water (30 mL) was treated with LiOH.H.sub.2O (0.93 g, 22.2 mmol) in water (10 mL).
#Text=Methanol was added until a transparent solution formed (20 mL).
#Text=C. for overnight and the organic solvents were removed under vacuum.
#Text=The residual aqueous solution was acidified with 2N HCl to pH 2 and was partitioned between ethyl acetate and water.
#Text=The organic phase was washed with water, dried (MgSO.sub.4), filtered and concentrated to give Example 10B as a white solid (3.8 g, 97% yield).
